II. Investor / Game-Theory Attack Simulations
Assume adversaries are smarter than you. Design accordingly.
1. Whale Dominance Attack
Goal: Acquire majority supply early
Vector:
Split capital across wallets (sybil)
Mitigation:
Quadratic allocation:
Plain text
allocation ∝ √stake
Identity weighting (optional)
Max cap per wallet cluster
2. Commit Manipulation Attack
Goal: Observe others, then adjust commitment
Vector:
Late commit sniping
Mitigation:
Strict commit deadline
Hash-based commitments (no visibility)
3. Reveal Griefing
Goal: Reduce competition by not revealing
Vector:
Commit → don’t reveal → distort pool
Mitigation:
Penalize non-reveal:
burn deposit
redistribute to honest participants
4. Entropy Prediction Attack
Goal: Predict ordering
Vector:
Control entropy source
Mitigation:
Multi-source entropy (ETH + BTC + beacon)
Delay entropy reveal until after commit phase
5. MEV / Front-Run Attack
Goal: Jump ahead in allocation or trading
Mitigation:
Commit/reveal hides intent
Batch settlement
Single execution block
6. Post-Launch Dump Attack
Goal: Crash price immediately
Vector:
Early participants exit
Mitigation:
Vesting tiers
Liquidity depth buffers
Treasury counterflow
7. Narrative Attack (Underrated)
Goal: Kill trust
Vector:
“It’s rigged” narrative
Mitigation:
Public verification dashboard
Reproducible proofs
Radical transparency
